<exercise checkit-seed="0008" checkit-slug="V7" checkit-title="Basis of a subspace">
  <statement>
    <p>
Consider the following subspace <m>W</m> of <m>\mathbb R^4</m>: 
<me>W=\mathrm{span}\,\left\{ \left[\begin{array}{c}
-2 \\
-1 \\
-1 \\
1
\end{array}\right] , \left[\begin{array}{c}
-5 \\
-3 \\
1 \\
0
\end{array}\right] , \left[\begin{array}{c}
14 \\
8 \\
0 \\
-2
\end{array}\right] , \left[\begin{array}{c}
-2 \\
-1 \\
0 \\
3
\end{array}\right] , \left[\begin{array}{c}
-3 \\
-2 \\
4 \\
3
\end{array}\right] \right\}.</me>
    </p>
    <ol>
        <li><p>Explain how to find a basis of <m>W</m>.</p></li>
        <li><p>Explain how to find the dimension of <m>W</m>.</p></li>
    </ol>
  </statement>
  <answer>
      <p><me>\mathrm{RREF}\,\left[\begin{array}{ccccc}
-2 &amp; -5 &amp; 14 &amp; -2 &amp; -3 \\
-1 &amp; -3 &amp; 8 &amp; -1 &amp; -2 \\
-1 &amp; 1 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 4 \\
1 &amp; 0 &amp; -2 &amp; 3 &amp; 3
\end{array}\right]=\left[\begin{array}{ccccc}
1 &amp; 0 &amp; -2 &amp; 0 &amp; -3 \\
0 &amp; 1 &amp; -2 &amp; 0 &amp; 1 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 1 &amp; 2 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0
\end{array}\right]</me></p>
     <ol>
          <li><p>A basis of <m>W</m> is <m>\left\{ \left[\begin{array}{c}
-2 \\
-1 \\
-1 \\
1
\end{array}\right] , \left[\begin{array}{c}
-5 \\
-3 \\
1 \\
0
\end{array}\right] , \left[\begin{array}{c}
-2 \\
-1 \\
0 \\
3
\end{array}\right] \right\}</m>.</p></li>
          <li><p>The dimension of <m>W</m> is <m>3</m>.</p></li>
      </ol>
  </answer>
</exercise>
